ze=1> Direct copy/paste from my posts to the other forums...  I can't even muster the strength for one last rant, I just don't care anymore.  Verant has denied me as a rogue for the last time, and they will have my money no longer.  Goodbye everyone. <BR>  <BR> ----- <BR>  <BR> OK Povar rogues, I am leaving EQ forever...  I won't go into my reasons for it here, since those types of posts seem to be unpopular with the new crowd..  Those of you who actually read this board or talk to me in-game on a daily basis probably already saw this coming, and anyone else can browse thru and see my recent posts to catch up if you give a damn. <BR>  <BR> I will say this however...  EQ is a game.  Games are meant to be fun.  If you are not enjoying yourself, either due to poor implentation of your chosen class, or just general disenchantment with the game mechanics, you need to re-evaluate and ask yourself why you are playing.  In the end, we all need to stay happy, and if this game isnt doing that for you, find something else to do with your time and your $10 a month. <BR>  <BR> Anyways, TONIGHT, thats THURSDAY NIGHT, I would like to organize a gathering of Povar rogues in Freeport for a &quot;Loot Modus&quot; fest.  I believe I will be logging on between 9 and 10 PST to take care of this.  I won't be staying on for too long, so if you want some free stuff, or just to say goodbye, please be there, as I will not be hanging out to wait for people (sorry).  Specifically, I have several items reserved for Vestas, Kaens, Deadron, and Stabsalot.  (I was planning on giving most of my stuff to my great friend Nanuudar, but he mentioned that he might be leaving too..  Nan, lemme know what your plans are, ok?  Bedrenken, you don't get jack.  hehe.  /hug)  Other Povar rogues are welcome to show up, introduce yourself, and I will give you what I can. <BR>  <BR> I also have a twinked monk in freeport named Gouken with some nice stuff on him, I will give that stuff to people too.  Finally, I have a Hu SK named Dredd and a DE Mage named Torch in Qeynos, so if anyone is out that way and is unable to make it to freeport, I will gladly give you the stuff on them as well.  (Otherwise I will just be dropping it all on the ground outside the Qeynos city gates.  Heh.) <BR>  <BR> So this is it, its been real...  I might still post here from time to time, but there has been so much negativity here lately (from myself included) that I can't even promise I will do that. <BR>  <BR> The Safehouse has been one of the best online communities I have ever been a part of.  You guys have really helped me stick it out this long, and the advice, fun, and comradery(sp) has been fantasctic.  I owe all of you a huge thanks and a big group hug, and I wish you all the best.  ;) <BR>  <BR> See you all in UT or Neverwinter Nights!  Safe journeys, and may life treat you well. <BR>  <BR> /bow <p><table cellspacing="2" cellpadding="2">
